<subSubSection id="4D2F63DDD0E274F03AEE0A7876FA6D09" pageId="5" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="ABBF8C7CAB365390DE64B74BE286F13D" pageId="5" pageNumber="24">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0947AB03898CC8F680D0212C6172BB4C" pageId="5" pageNumber="24">
The species epithet is derived from 
<emphasis id="BF30F7E68C9E332F6061BDAEF6F6E65A" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="24">Sino</emphasis>
-, pertaining to China, and 
<emphasis id="1313BC65E912F292F029256D9E179179" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="24">aestivum</emphasis>
, reflecting the sectional placement of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
